@mrlubos For the example of generic:

```ts
interface User {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}

useForm<User>();

```

With yup, I am already doing this for each form

```tsx
const schema: ObjectSchema<Values> = object({
  name: string().required()
}).defined()

useForm({
  defaultValues: {
    name: ''
  },
  resolver: yupResolver(schema)
})
```

Would I have to now use `Values` also in `useForm<Values>({ ... })`? Is there any way to simplify my syntax? Feels a bit redundant to duplicate the same type annotation

